<section xml:id="how-to-learn" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>How to learn?</title>
  <subsection>
    <title>Showcase: softwares</title>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Choose a software listed below. All of them run in browsers so you don't need to install them.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Find tutorials and look for typical usages of the software. For graphical calculators plotting <m> x^2 + y^2 - z^2 = -1 </m> might be a start. For computer algebra systems evaluating <m> \int_0^{\pi} \sin^4 x \mathop{\mathrm{d}\!} x </m> might be a start.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Think about how the software can be useful to you. Search online for interesting or novel usages of the software.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Come up with a very specific example where the software is useful. Test it out and share your experience! Demonstrate what the software is good at and what the limitations are.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
